<p>Dignity = originated from rank (dignitaries in medieval europe) =&gt; rank based dignity == not for all =&gt; material benfits for dignitaries&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Kant =&gt; Dignity is for all. Why? Dignity recognises human capacity to progress and set-and-act in one's own moral standards.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>dignity = preamble to CoI&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Dignity and peace&nbsp;</h3>
<p>dignity&nbsp; = bundle of values = tolerance, mutual respect, respect for diversity, solidarity,&nbsp;</p>
<p>peace = set of traditions, values, behaviours that promote understanding, goodwill.</p>